Title : City Hall (Columbia, Missouri)
Text : [[File:CoMo Daniel Boone tavern.jpg|thumb|The 1917 structure restored]]
[[File:CoMo city hall front.jpg|thumb|The 2011 addition and public art]]
'''City Hall''' in [[Columbia, Missouri]], also known as the '''Daniel Boone Building''', was built in 1917. A major addition and restoration was completed in 2011, along with a matching five-story structure.<ref>http://www.voxmagazine.com/blog/2011/03/historic-daniel-boone-building-rededicated/</ref> Originally built as a hotel, it has functioned as the city hall of Columbia since 1972 by (respectively) replacing the municipal building across the street.<ref>http://www.waymarking.com/gallery/image.aspx?f=1&guid=3199ee36-8b9c-48a0-a6ff-de6b74b88cf6</ref><ref>http://www.emporis.com/building/daniel-boone-building-columbia-mo-usa</ref> The building is a contributing property on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in the [[Downtown Columbia, Missouri]] historic district and is at the intersection of Broadway  and the [[Avenue of the Columns]]. The chambers of the [[Columbia City Council]] are on the ground floor.

